{"TopicId":11165,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Carrier XR-15","CreatedByName":"edsupagood","CreatedById":4288,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-05-22T01:06:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"edsupagood","CreatedById":4288,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-05-22T01:06:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EJust a little carrier plane I built. Very stable and easy to control. You are able to separate the top plane and fly once at a high altitude.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img850.imageshack.us/img850/4195/carrier01.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022carrier01.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img853.imageshack.us/img853/818/carrier02.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022carrier02.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://img20.imageshack.us/img20/1143/carrier03.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022carrier03.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMake sure to use SAS to make more stable.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E1. Take off and climb to a high altitude (up to you how high)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E2. Level out, and press space to start up the engine on the smaller plane.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E3. When engine is running at 100 percent, press space again to separate, and pull up to avoid a collision.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Thobewill10","CreatedById":6148,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-05-22T01:07:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe pictures aren\\\u0027t showing up. Might you try to reupload them?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"edsupagood","CreatedById":4288,"CreatedDateTime":"2012-05-22T01:09:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\\\u0027ll do that. Sorry\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}